#!/bin/bash

# archy:summary=Print a security notice before installing AUR packages

cat <<'EOF'

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Installing packages from the AUR (Arch User Repository)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  The AUR is user-submitted and is NOT signed or vetted like the official
  Arch repos. It has been a real malware vector (CHAOS RAT 2025, Spark RAT
  2025, the "Atomic Arch" mass-hijack of orphaned packages 2026).

  To stay safe, this setup:
    • routes everything available in the signed repos through pacman, not AUR
    • ships only actively-maintained AUR packages that pull from their genuine,
      official upstream (none were in the Atomic Arch blast radius)
    • reviews each PKGBUILD/.install interactively when you run an AUR install
      by hand. Unattended runs (like this logged installer, which has no TTY)
      build the pre-vetted list above without prompts.

  Run `archy-pkg-aur-add <pkg>` later in a terminal to review a PKGBUILD diff
  before building. Full details in SECURITY.md.
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

EOF
sleep 2
